The user is asking me to respond to each of these statements as if I am a primary or secondary school teacher from Spain responding to a survey about AI in education.

I need to provide responses to all 10 statements using the response options: 'Strongly disagree', 'Disagree', 'Agree', 'Strongly agree', 'I don't know'.

Let me think about each statement from the perspective of a thoughtful Spanish teacher:

TT4G35A: "Artificial intelligence helps teachers write or improve lesson plans." - I would AGREE. AI tools can indeed help with brainstorming and improving lesson plans.

TT4G35B: "Artificial intelligence enables teachers to adapt learning material to different students' abilities." - I would AGREE. AI can help personalize content for different learning levels.

TT4G35C: "Artificial intelligence assists teachers in supporting students individually." - I would AGREE. AI can help provide personalized support and feedback.

TT4G35D: "Artificial intelligence supports students with specific needs (e.g. multilingual learners, students with special education needs)." - I would AGREE. AI has potential to help support diverse learners.

TT4G35E: "Artificial intelligence helps teachers automate administrative tasks." - I would STRONGLY AGREE. This is a clear benefit - grading, attendance tracking, etc.

TT4G35F: "Artificial intelligence enables students to misrepresent others' work as their own." - I would AGREE. This is a real concern with AI-generated content. Students could use AI to pass off generated work as their own.

TT4G35G: "Artificial intelligence makes recommendations that may not be appropriate or correct." - I would AGREE. AI can make errors and inappropriate suggestions.

TT4G35H: "Artificial intelligence amplifies biases that reinforce students' misconceptions." - I would AGREE. AI systems can perpetuate biases present in training data.

TT4G35I: "Artificial intelligence jeopardises the privacy and security of student data." - I would AGREE. 

Data protection is a genuine concern when using AI systems in educational settings. TT4G35J: "Artificial intelligence suggests unsuitable pedagogical approaches that teachers would use with students." - I would AGREE. AI recommendations don't always align with sound teaching practices, so I lean toward this position.
